        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Require Evaluation before Implementing Executive Wishlists Act of 2022 or the REVIEW Act of 202</b><strong>2</strong></p> <p>This bill prohibits a final agency rule from taking effect until (1) the agency submits the rule to the Office of Information and Regulatory Affairs (OIRA), and (2) OIRA makes a determination as to whether the rule is a high-impact rule that may impose an annual cost on the economy of at least $1 billion.</p> <p>In addition, an agency must postpone the effective date of a high-impact rule until the final disposition of all actions seeking judicial review of the rule.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
